to the editor joel m gora and peter j wallison op ed march 17 link the right to push large sums of money into political slush funds with free speech indeed if one is to argue for our current system of legalized bribery this is the way to go who is going to argue against the right to free speech but what about this notion that money is speech perhaps with the advent of the information economy we will become more and more comfortable with the abstraction that expression is actually a form of spending and learning is a form of purchasing in this scenario it is reasonable to believe that unlimited amounts of cash are needed for unlimited political expression in any case a cringing glance at my monthly bank statement lets me know where i stand in this debate g k darby new orleans march 18 2001

